{"type":"message","id":"c231595c","parentId":"0b4d8a7f","timestamp":"2026-04-06T18:23:37.941Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand - the user doesn't have proper logging set up. The new process failed immediately because port was in use (the old one was still running), so there's no useful log.\n\nLet me help them understand the issue:\n\n1. The Router v3.0 has intent detection (`/api/intent`) and scoring (`/api/score`) - both work\n2. The scoring happens when messages go through the Router\n3. But from the webchat channel (the current session), messages probably go directly to Gateway, not through Router\n\nLet me check how webchat messages are processed - if they bypass Router entirely, that would explain why there's no scoring log.\n\nActually wait - let me think about the architecture:\n- The current session is webchat (not via Router)\n- Messages from webchat → Gateway → OpenClaw\n- The scoring API needs to be explicitly called by someone\n\nLooking at the AGENTS.md again:\n- \"消息以 @p 开头时自动调用评分 API 并返回结果\"\n\nSo scoring is triggered by a prefix `@p` or by the code explicitly calling it. Let me check if there's auto-scoring middleware or if the Gateway calls the scoring API.\n\nLet me check the Gateway config and see how messages flow:\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3fc7fc2f5a734d97bcc710a3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json 2>/dev/null | head -50"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"codingplan","model":"minimax-m2.5","usage":{"input":18529,"output":294,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18823,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775499813678,"responseId":"chatcmpl-561ed048-254e-4c81-8748-47a784b33eb4"}}
